[White "Introduction"]
[Black "Introduction to the Philidor Defense"]
[Result "*"]

{ ¡Hello and welcome to the course!  First of all I would like to thank you for getting the course. I have worked really hard during the last months to find the best variations for you.   In this introduction video I want to talk about the structure of my course.  This is a Lifetime Repertoire against e4, based in the Philidor Defense, but we will play and learn more than just the Philidor in some lines when White deviates.   You will find these sections in the following Chapters:  - 1.e4 d6 and the Main move to get into the Philidor, 2.d4   - 1.e4 d6 and a wide range of second moves for White such as: g3, some Maroczy setups with c4, Nf3 which leads to King's Indian Attack and I will show you how to play against this system.  - 1.e4 d6 and 2.Nc3 or 2.f4 , we can get there by transposition and we will cover it in one Chapter.  - 1.e4 d6 and Bc4 which is more rare but not it is not good for White.  Then we will get into de Philidor Defense by studying the mainline and the endgame variation.  This endgame Chapter is a long one and I will show you how to play it during two hours of video. Some people say it is a drawish line, but it is not! If you know what you are doing with your pieces you can get an edge and you will have very interesting games.  Then we have three more Chapters. We will cover the mainlines after Nge2-Be7. White can play h3, g3 and f3, trying to play some English Attack systems.   Finally, we will go into the Mainline after 4.Nf3   There, I cover the main two options for Black. You don't need to study all of them, you can choose which Block to study and then if you have more time, you can study the second one.  - In the first block I will talk about the "Open Philidor" 4...exd4   - In the second block I will discuss the 4...Nbd7 variation, my favourite.  4...Nbd7 is the line that I have played along my whole chess career. By the way, I have played more than 100 classical chess games with the Philidor! Hopefully I can transfer some of my experience to you guys.  We will have a look into one of my favourite Chapters, 5.g4! which creates a lot of complications and fun games arise after this sequence.  Being said that, I hope you enjoy the course and if you have any questions I will gladly help you in the comments. Have fun and see you in the next Chapters! }
1. -- *

