{ In this variarions, the kings will be in opposite flanks. The game will continue as an exciting race and as usually, the one arriving first wins! }
8. O-O-O Nxd4 9. Qxd4 Be6
{ black develops the bishop and is ready to start pushing with a6 and b5. White will do the same on the kingside. }
10. f3
{ The main line. White prepares for a kingside expansion with g4.   10.Kb1  a6  11.f3  transposes   10.Qd2  a6  11.f3  transposes }
10... a6 11. Qd2 { Prophylaxis against c5. } 11... b5 12. Kb1 c6
{ repeating the idea of the main line! Black wants to push with d5. } 13. Bxd6
Bxd6 14. Qxd6 Qa5
{ and black has tremendous counterplay. b4 is a threat again. } 15. a3 Rfd8 16.
Qb4
{ was seen in Solodovnichenko,Y @@StartBracket@@2572@@EndBracket@@ -Brynell,S @@StartBracket@@2408@@EndBracket@@ ½-½ Sweden 2020 and here we suggest the novelty }
16... Qb6 { better than Qc7 to keep and eye on the c5 square. } 17. Be2 c5
{ 17...a5  18.Qe7  Rdb8  with fantastic play and an equal and unbalanced position. Ideas: h6 followed by Ra7. a4-b4 as well, etc. I would not like to be in white's skin! }
18. Na4 *

