10... b5 { a typical reaction in the Philidor. } 11. axb6 Nxb6
{ This is the key. The bishop on c4 is hanging. Now black is on time to fight for the d5 square. }
12. Bb3 cxd5 13. exd5
{ 13.Nxd5  Nfxd5  14.exd5  Bg4  black was slightly better in Perske,T @@StartBracket@@2448@@EndBracket@@ -Predojevic,B @@StartBracket@@2626@@EndBracket@@ ½-½ Germany 2019. All these positions where white cannot finally place a piece on d5 are great for black. There is a nasty pin on f3 that is not easy to handle for white. }
13... a5 { with the idea of Bd7-Qc7 and black has a very nice position. } *

