{ White needs to control the center. This was seen in Munoz Pantoja,M @@StartBracket@@2442@@EndBracket@@ -Narciso Dublan,M @@StartBracket@@2492@@EndBracket@@ 1-0 Barbera del Valles 2020 and I recommend you to play the aggresive move }
8... h5
{ White has now two natural ways of winning a tempo by hitting the queen. } 9.
c4 { The best move in my opinion gaining a lot of space in the center. } 9...
Qd6 10. g5 { White needs to do something about the opening of the h-file. }
10... e6 11. Nc3 O-O-O { attacking d4. } 12. Be3 Nge7
{ There we go! Black intends Nf5 putting a lot of pressure against d4 and e3. }
13. c5
{ The best move. White weakens the d5-square but at the same time will try to create troubles along the a4-e8 diagonal. }
13... Qd7 14. Qa4 Nd5 { White gave us the square so we should go for it! } 15.
O-O-O Be7 16. Bb5 { Once again, White intends to play Ne5. } 16... f6
{ And White should act quickly since positionally is worse. } 17. Bxc6
{ The endgame reached after } 17... Qxc6 18. Qxc6
{ 18.Qxa7  runs into  Nxc3  19.bxc3  Qxf3-+  winning material. } 18... bxc6
{ Is slightly better for Black.   The black king does not suffer anymore and the bishop pair and especially the light squared bishop is super strong. }
