6... g6 7. Nge2 Bh6
{ This will be our idea! Black will exchange the dark squared bishop. } 8. a3
Nf6 9. d3 Bxc1 10. Qxc1 O-O 11. Rb1
{ was seen in Di Berardino,D @@StartBracket@@2282@@EndBracket@@ -Bittencourt,J @@StartBracket@@2303@@EndBracket@@ ½-½ Brasilia 2003 and now black can play }
11... a6 12. b4 cxb4 13. axb4 b5 14. cxb5 axb5
{ and we do no need to worry about the capture on b5. } 15. O-O Bg4 16. f3 Be6
{ black is fine and readdy to push d5 at some point. The good thing of having provoked h4 is that after the natural push f4, g4 will be always be a weak square for the rest of the game. }
