1. e4
{ In this chapter, we cover the move  1...--  2.c4  . White may want to continue with  --  3.d4  occupying all the center or go for the Botvinnik System @@StartBracket@@Nc3, g3, Bg2, Nge2, etc.@@EndBracket@@.   I have found very interesting and aggressive recipes, so no more talk and let's go straight to the point! }
1... d6 2. c4 e5
{ Once we have played this move, black should avoid arriving to Maroczy-type positions and that means stopping white to play d4 followed by Nxf3. At this point, white has three options.   Some people will try  3.Nf3  aiming to go for  --  4.d4  . Others will go for the Botvinnik System and another bunch of people will try  3.d4  straightaway. }
3. Nc3 c5 4. g3 { 4.Nf3  transposes to 3.Nf3. } 4... Nc6 5. Bg2
{ White goes for the Botvinnik system.   Now I suggest a very aggresive try that will probably surprise your opponnent.   5...g6  leads to the main lines but my recommendation is   5.d3  h5  transposes to 5.Bg2 }
