{ This is the move we are hoping our opponent plays. Black will enjoy excellent play on the dark squares in the resulting positions. }
6... h4 7. g4
{ was seen in Praznik,A @@StartBracket@@2241@@EndBracket@@-Pantovic,D @@StartBracket@@2153@@EndBracket@@ ½-½ Velden 2008 and now we recommend to play }
7... Nge7 { black focuses all its play around the dark squares and f4. } 8.
Nge2 Ng6 9. O-O Be7 10. d3 O-O
{ and the black bishop is ready to land on g5. Trading the dark squared bishops is a great plan since our bishop does not have very good diagonals. By doing it, white will have very weak dark squares. }
11. Nd5 Bg5 12. Be3
{ taking on g5 would be a positional mistake. White offers the trade on e3 so at least after an eventual fxe3, white gains control on f4 and d4. }
12... Nd4 13. Qd2 Nxe2+ 14. Qxe2 Be6 15. Qd2 Bxe3
{ 15...f6!?  is playable as well. } 16. fxe3 a6
{ and black is completely fine and ready to look for b5 on the queenside. } *

