{ Hi all!   In this new chapter, we cover 2.Bc4. In my opinion, it is a harmless move and black gets very healthy positions from the very beginning.   Black has not defined the structure on the center with e5 yet, so since that the bishop is on c4, we will go for an early e6 followed by d5, winning tempo and neutralizing the bishop on the a2-g8 diagonal. }
