{ has been played in 17 games and at this point, we suggest deviating with the novelty }
7... Bc5 8. dxe6 Bxe6 9. Nf3
{ 9.Bf4  Nd5  10.Ne2  Nc6  Reinforcing d4. Black is ready to play a6 followed by O-O with very good play. }
9... Nc6 10. O-O a6 11. Na3 h6
{ black stops Bg5 and has better coordination and more space. } *

