{ Hi all!   Hope you recharged your batteries for this new chapter!   In this case, we cover the lines where white starts with  2.f4  or  2.Nc3  .  Sometimes it leads to positions that have many similarities with the King's Gambit, Vienna Gambit or even closed Sicilians. }
1... d6 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. d4 e5 { and now we just cover the move } 4. f4
{ which has not been covered in the previous chapters. I decided to do it in this one because here we analyze all the lines where White goes for an early f4. This move has been tried by several GMs, so it deserves some attention. }
