{ once black is castled, the white queen is under attack. } 8. Bxc6 bxc6 9. O-O
c5 10. Qd3 { and here I suggest the novelty } 10... a5 { threatening Ba6. } 11.
e5
{ is a natural move trying to ruin black's pawn structure.   If White plays  11.Re1  Ba6  12.Qd1  Re8  black has very good play. Idea: Bb7, Bf8, Nd7, etc. }
11... dxe5 12. fxe5 Qxd3 13. cxd3 Nd7 14. Bf4 a4
