{ and black takes advantage of the white's king situation in the center. } 8.
Nge2 dxe4 9. dxe4 Ng4
{ Bh4+ is in the air.  10.O-O  is not possible due to  Bc5+  followed by Nf2. }
10. Qxd8 Rxd8 11. h3 Bh4+ 12. Kf1 Nf2 13. Rg1
{ and the knight cannot go back but finds a nice square on d1! } 13... Nd1
{ Black wants to complete development with Nc6 and Be6. } 14. f5
{ 14.Nd5?!  is inaccurate due to  Na6!-+  followed by c6. It is so cool that the knight on d1 cannot be attacked :@@EndBracket@@ }
14... Nxc3 15. Nxc3 Nc6
{ And the position is around equal with precise moves for white even though I find it a bit easier to play with the black pieces. The knight is arriving at d4 with good play. }
