{ Black's idea is to play e5, aiming to trade queens.   12...h6!?  13.Nf3  Nh7=+  followed by f5 is also fine for Black. }
13. e5 { White forgets about a check on d4! } 13... dxe5 14. fxe5 Qd4+ 15. Be3
Qxe5 16. Rxf6 { Looks winning for White but... } 16... h6 17. Rxf7 Bxg5 18.
Rxf8+ Rxf8
{ And Black has a big advantage. The white king is in real trouble.   The c6-bishop and the f8-rook are great attacking pieces. }
*

