{ This position reminds me of a good version of the classical French for Black where White has a poor bishop on a2 and White did not manage to play d4. }
11. Qe1 { and now Black has two interesting choices. } 11... b5
{ The first engine option. White can try the aggresive } 12. f5 Kh8 13. Qg3
{ 13.fxe6  fxe6=+ } 13... b4 14. Ne2 exf5 15. Bf4
{ 15.Bxd5?  runs into  Ndxe5-+  and the d5 bishop is hanging. } 15... Ndb8
{ Black is a pawn up but White has some compensation. I would still take Black with no doubt. }
