a3 { Prophylaxis against Na5. } 8... Be6 9. Nd5 Bxd5 10. exd5 Ne5
{ using the fact that after the trades d5 will also be hanging. } 11. Ba2
{ Rozkov,N @@StartBracket@@2422@@EndBracket@@-Smirnova,A @@StartBracket@@2079@@EndBracket@@ 1-0 Nizhnij Novgorod 2012 }
11... Nfd7 12. O-O Nxf3+ 13. Qxf3 Bg5 14. Bg3 Bd2
{ And this move is pretty precise. The idea of this precise move is to stop Rae1 while allowing the queen to join the game via g5. White has the bishop pair, but the a2 bishop is blocked by its own d5 pawn. Overall, Black is slightly better, and will follow up with ...Qg5 and ...Rae8.   White has the bishop pair but the a2 bishop is blocked by its own d5 pawn. }
