a3 { Prophylaxis against Na5. } 8... Be6 9. Nd5 Bxd5 10. exd5 Ne5
{ using the fact that after the trades d5 will also be hanging. } 11. Nxe5 dxe5
12. Bxe5
{ was seen in Popov,V @@StartBracket@@2555@@EndBracket@@-Malakhov,V @@StartBracket@@2702@@EndBracket@@ 1/2-1/2 St Petersburg 2015 and we propose the novelty }
12... Bd6 13. Bxd6 Re8+
{ A nice intermediate move! White now loses the right to castle. } 14. Kd2 Qxd6
15. Qf3 Qe5 16. c3 Qg5+ 17. Kc2 Re3 18. h4 Qe5 19. d4 Qe7 20. Qf4 Re8
{ Black intends to play ...Qd7 and ...Nxd5, and White will never be able to fight for the e-file. }
