{ We all expect White to go  6.d4  but White has other options that need to be analyzed as well. }
6. d4 { This position can be reached as well via the King's Gambit! } 6... Nxe4
{ Black uses the fork on d5 again. } 7. Bxf7+
{ This move is very tempting for White players but if Black consolidates, Black will be just better. }
7... Kxf7 8. Nxe4
{ and I give you two options now. One is safer and the other one is more aggressive and forces White to take difficult decisions. Up to you! }
