1. e4 d6 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. c3
{ This might seem to you a pretty weird move but it is a very interesting try.   White's idea could be to play  3...--  4.Qc2  if Black does not respond properly and then install a beautiful center after  4...--  5.d4  Naturally, if black plays  3...c5  we are transposing to an Alapin variation. No need to say that  3...Nxe4?  loses because of  Qa4+ }
3... e5 { and we analyze five different moves now. } 4. Qc2
{ played by Russian GM Antipov among others. White wants to play d4. We deviate from all main lines with the move }
4... d5 { which has only been played in one game. } 5. exd5
{ is dubious because of } 5... e4 6. Nd4 Qxd5
{ and black is ready to continue development with Bc5 and Nc6. Black has an space advantage. }
