{ 8.Be3?  is the main line but Black is clearly better after  8...d5  9.exd5  Nxd5  followed by Bf5 and Qd7    Was seen in Del Corro,J-Gonzalez,J ½-½ Mexico 1999 and I like now }
8... Ne8
{ Black has a slightly easier play. The idea is to push f5.   Nc7 is coming and from there Black can also look for a6-b5 or Ne6. }
