{ Reaching very double edged positions.   One of the good news is that in practice it is very easy to go wrong for White and he has gone wrong in many tournament games. }
6. e5 { The only reasonable move at this point. } 6... Nh5
{ The best move even though  6...Nfd7  is the main line. Black is threatening Qh4 now. Out of 14 games, white went wrong in 6 now, including strong GMs. }
7. Nc3
{ white intends to create some counterplay against the c7 pawn after the queen lands on h1. }
7... Qh4+ 8. g3 Nxg3 9. hxg3 Qxh1 10. Nxd5 Na6 11. Nb5
{ but black is better after } 11... Bb4+ { with the idea of Ba5, covering c7. }
12. Nxb4 { does not work because of } 12... Bh3 13. Qe2 Nxb4 14. Nxc7+ Kf8 15.
Nxa8 Bxf1 { and c2 falls. } *

