{ The best move even though  6...Nfd7  is the main line. Black is threatening Qh4 now. Out of 14 games, white went wrong in 6 now, including strong GMs. }
7. g3 { The only precise move. stopping Qh4. } 7... c5
{ The most direct attemp.   And after this move the strongest players with the white pieces went for a dubious line :@@EndBracket@@. Try to think at home what would be your next move with white.   7...g6!?  is also possible.  8.Nc3  c6  9.Bg2  Ng7  with a complex position. }
8. Nb3
{ This innacurate move has been played the same number of times than  8.Nb5  and by the stronger white players that reached this position.   That means good news for us :@@EndBracket@@ We now suggest the novelty }
8... Nc6 9. f4 { white protects e5.   9.g4?  is not possible due to  Qh4+ }
9... g6 10. Bg2 { this natural move allows } 10... c4 11. Nd4 Qb6
{ the pressure along the a7-g1 diagonal is too strong after } 12. c3 Bc5
{ and the diagonal gets opened. black is clearly better. } *

