8. Nb3
{ This innacurate move has been played the same number of times than  8.Nb5  and by the stronger white players that reached this position.   That means good news for us :@@EndBracket@@ We now suggest the novelty }
8... Nc6 9. f4 { white protects e5.   9.g4?  is not possible due to  Qh4+ }
9... g6 10. Nc3 { white's idea is to play Ne4 in case black pushes d4. } 10...
Be6 11. Bg2 { black again tries to gain control on the a7-g1 diagonal after }
11... c4 12. Nd4 Qb6 13. Be3 Bc5 14. Nxe6 fxe6 15. Bxc5 Qxc5
{ black has a dreaming position. The idea is to proceed with 0-0-0 and Ng7-f5. }
