{ 9.Na3  Hertneck,G  (2508)  -Belkhodja,S  (2476)  1-0 Germany 2008. Here we suggest to continue with  9...Bg4  Novelty  10.Nc2  c6  with equality The knight was not developed yet to c6, so it was possible to reinforce the pawn center. Black will finish development with Nbd7 }
9... Nc6 10. Nbd2
{ we have transposed to a game that was played in different order. Now I like }
10... Nd7 { forcing white to play } 11. Bf4 g5 12. Bg3 g4 13. Nd4 Ndxe5 14.
Nxc6 Nxc6 { 15.Bxg4  runs into  f5-+  followed by f4, winning a piece. } 15. f3
gxf3 16. Bxf3 Bd6
{ and black is a pawn up but white has some compensation. The position is still very double edged.   Idea: Bf5 followed by Ne7. }
*

