{ 9...Be7  is the main line by far, which means that the proposed move will probbaly get your opponent out of book. White tried four alternatives at this crossroads. }
10. Re1 Be7 11. h3 Bh5
{ and white cannot develop easily if it is not by moving the knight from d2. }
12. Ne4 dxc3
{ and there is a tempting tactics for white right now. In the two games played with this position white went for it and ended up clearly worse after }
13. Qxd8+ { 13.Nxc5  Qxd1  transposes to 12.Nb3. } 13... Rxd8 14. Nf6+
{ tempting but horrible! } 14... gxf6 15. exf6 Bxf3
{ and the knight sooner or later will end up on d4 with fatal consequences for white. }
16. gxf3
{ Bakhtadze,G @@StartBracket@@2275@@EndBracket@@ -Rowson,J @@StartBracket@@2400@@EndBracket@@ 0-1 Holon 1995 }
16... Rd6 { forcing white to take } 17. fxe7 Nd4
{ and white can resign again. c2 and f3 targetted. } *

