5... O-O 6. Be3
{ Is also a natural move. Once that h3 has been played, Ng4 is not possible. }
6... c6
{ This is always a useful move. Black prepares an expansion on the queenside and supports a possible d5. }
7. a4
{ is the other line that we should cover. It has been seen in several games. White stops black expansion. Black gets nice play immediately. This was seen for instance in Djurhuus, R @@StartBracket@@2598@@EndBracket@@-Eriksson, M @@StartBracket@@2431@@EndBracket@@ 0-1 Sweden 2006 and we recommend the novelty }
7... Na6 { The b4 square is wonderful! } 8. Qd2 { is too slow } 8... Nb4 9. g4
{ Once the knight is on b4 supporting d5 it is time to strike in the center! }
9... exd4 10. Nxd4 d5 11. e5 Nd7
{ and something has gone wrong for white. Nxe5 and c5 followed by d4 are big threats. }
12. Nf3 f5 { and black is clearly better. } *

