7. Bxf7 Rf8 8. Bb3 Nxe4 { black gets the pawn back } 9. Ne2
{ and we propose the novelty } 9... Nc5
{ 9...Nxf2  is dubious and I experienced some pain over the board with this move. I had a very difficult position after  10.Rf1  Ng4  11.Bg5+  Ke8  12.O-O-O  Rxf1  13.Rxf1  h6  14.Nd5  Bd6  15.Be7  Bxe7  16.Nxc7  Kd8  17.Nxa8  and white was better in Martinez Ramirez,E @@StartBracket@@2206@@EndBracket@@-Cuenca Jimenez, J @@StartBracket@@2493@@EndBracket@@ 1/2-1/2 19th Open A 2011   @@StartBracket@@  10.O-O?!  is not correct because of  Bc5!  @@EndBracket@@ }
10. O-O Nxb3 11. axb3 Be6 12. Be3
{ 12.Bg5+?!  helps Black since  Kc8  is anyway part of the plan. } 12... b6 13.
f4 { is the critical test } 13... Kc8 14. fxe5 Nc6 15. Nf4 Bg8 16. Ncd5 Re8
{ And Black wins the e5-pawn back with a 0.00 position. } *

