7. Bd2
{ is the mainline. White protects the c3-knight and is ready to capture with the bishop, keeping a healthy pawn structure. }
7... Ke7 8. Nge2 c6 { we are ready to start a pawn march on the queen side } 9.
O-O-O b5 10. Bb3 Bc5 11. f3 a5 12. a4 b4 13. Na2 Nbd7
{ with good play. The bishop can be placed on b6 so the c5 square is available for a knight. Whenever white goes Ng3, we stop Nf5 with the simple move g6. }
