{ White did not go for Bc4, so no more chances baby! } 8. O-O-O Nd7 9. Nb5
{ grabbing the bishop pair } 9... Ke7 10. Nxd6 cxd6
{ With a very healthy position. This is essentially an Open Sicilian.  Despite having lost the bishop pair, Black has a fantastic center, pressure on e4 and and opened c-file to create counterplay.   The two bishops are not very dangerous in this position. }
11. Nd2 h6 12. Bh4 g5 13. Bg3 Nh5 14. f3 Nxg3 { Rac8 and h5 coming. } 15. hxg3
