5... Kxd8 6. Bg5
{ Probably the most natural move in this position. White pins the knight and is ready to castle long winning another tempo. Now we propose two ways to play. }
6... Be6
{ This is the most solid approach for Black. Black's idea is to develop the knight to d7 later. The Bishop on e6 does a great job covering f7. }
