{ This is the critical line. White goes for the direct approach. It is important to remember all these lines and understand the ideas properly. }
8... exf4 9. Nf3 Kc8 10. Bxf4
{ Black has to be very careful now because Nb5 is a strong idea. } 10... Bc5
{ Prophylaxis against Nb5   10...Ng4?!  11.Nb5!  Nf2  12.Nxc7  Nxh1  13.Nxa8  Nf2  14.Re1+= }
11. e5 Ng4 12. Ne4 Be3+ 13. Bxe3 Nxe3 14. Re1 Nxf1 15. Rhxf1
{ And here we come up with this interesting novelty } 15... a5
{ The idea is to protect the bishop on e6 from the third rank   15...h6?!  16.Nd4  Nxe5  17.Nxe6  fxe6  18.Nc5+- }
16. Nfg5 Ra6 17. Nxf7 Re8 18. Nfg5 h6 19. Nf3 Bg4
{ and Black gets the pawn back with equality. } *

