9. Be3
{ This is the most aggressive line. Black is well prepared to start an attack on the queenside. }
9... Nbd7 10. g4
{ This novelty is a very direct approach and the first recommendation from Stockfish12 after a short thought. It has never been played but is great to be prepared against it just in case our opponent arrives with home preparation :@@EndBracket@@ White goes all-in on the kingside without having castled. The idea is to push g5 sending the knight to a bad square. }
10... g6 11. Qf4 { 11.Qf3?  runs into  Ne5  and g4 falls. } 11... d5
