1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 exd4 5. Nxd4 Be7 6. g3
{ Welcome back!   In this chapter, we analyze one of the most trendy lines in the Philidor with 4...exd4.   As you already know, 2020 has been an explosion for online chess and there have been many online super tournaments. The Magnus tour and the Champions Chess Tour have gathered the best chess players in the World competing almost every month.   In these tournaments, we have seen the World Champion Magnus Carlsen and his friend Daniil Dubov playing our beloved Philidor defense with success. In those games, 6.g3 was one of the main weapons employed by the white players.   No more talk and let's get to work! }
6... O-O 7. Bg2 Re8 8. O-O Bf8 { and white has several choices at this point. }
9. Bf4
{ White develops the bishop to a very natural square and gets ready to play Qd2 connecting the rooks. }
9... c6 10. Re1 Nbd7 11. h3 Ne5
{ a good square for the knight once the white dark squared bishop is on f4 and does not allow f4. }
12. g4
{ 12.a4  transposes to  @@StartFEN@@r1bqrbk1/pp1n1ppp/2pp1n2/8/3NPB2/2N3P1/PPP2PBP/R2QR1K1 w - - 2 11@@EndFEN@@  11.a4 }
12... g6
{ A good prophylactic move giving the h5 square for the knight in case White pushes g5. White tried two moves at this point. }
13. Bg3 { makes sense preparing f4. } 13... h5 14. g5
{ This was seen in Khamrakulov,D @@StartBracket@@2524@@EndBracket@@-Niyazmetov,R @@StartBracket@@2227@@EndBracket@@ 1-0 Tashkent 2009 and here we need to remember a very important precise move. }
14... h4 15. Bxh4 Nh5
{ black sacrifices a pawn but has fantastic counterplay. f4 is a tasty square for the knight. There are tactical shots on h3 followed by Nf3+ in certain lines. Nc4 targetting b2 and Be7 attacking g5 are attractive ideas as well. }
16. Qc1
{ This the first move that came to my mind when I was thinking over the board about this position. White covers f4. The queen on d2 is more exposed to moves like Nc4. }
16... Qb6 { and white's only move here is } 17. Nb3 { allows } 17... Bxh3
{ boom! } 18. Bxh3 Nf3+ 19. Kf1 Nxh4 { with a big advantage. } *

