Rfe1 Ng6 16. Be3 d5 17. exd5 Bb4 { white suffers along the a5-e1 diagonal! }
18. dxc6 bxc6 { Nd5 is a big threat difficult to stop. } 19. Bf4 Rxe1+ 20. Qxe1
Bh3 { 20...Nxf4=+  is also enough to get an edge. } 21. Be3 Bxg2 22. Kxg2 c5
23. Nde2 Ne5
{ White suffers along the light squares. Qc6 and Qf5 are strong ideas. } *

