{ The move that we all expect. It was played by Karjakin against the King Magnus in November 2020. }
12... Nfd7 13. f4 { white stops Ne5. } 13... a5 14. Be3
{ We are following Karjakin,S @@StartBracket@@2752@@EndBracket@@-Carlsen,M @@StartBracket@@2862@@EndBracket@@ 1-0 chess24.com INT 2020 and we deviate from the game with the strong.   14...Qc7  is the main line but I think White is just better. }
14... Nb6 { Black looks for d5 and puts an eye on the c4 square! } 15. b3
{ In order to control the c4 square, was played by Indian GM Negi, a recognized theoretician. }
15... d5 { there we go again! } 16. e5 Ne6 17. Nxe6 Bxe6 18. Ne2
{ White reroutes the knight, which had no good squares to reach from c3. }
18... Nc8
{ We have seen this idea already. The knight will be greatly placed on f5! }
19. Nd4 Ne7 { followed by Nf5 with good play. } *

