10. Nc7
{ This is all forced. We have to be ready to sacrifice a rook. Who dares to say that the Philidor is boring? Let's party! }
10... Nxe4
{ And now White has two possibilities and both have been played more or less the same. Black is using all it can against the white king. We have to take in count that our a8 rook is completely lost. }
11. Qe3
{ If you are checking this line with the engine, it will say +1.50 at the beginning. You have to let it run till depth 45-60 and will say 0.00. That is why supercomputers are so important nowadays in critical lines. }
11... Nxc3 12. bxc3 Ba3+ 13. Kd2
{ Is one of our options. Strong players like Volokitin chose it.   White will have to be very careful not to end up worse. }
13... Nd7 14. Nxa8
{ Again, I would like to say that it is important to memorize these chapter lines because we are in the streets with a rook down. But again, the good news is that Black is perfectly fine! }
14... Bc5
{ After this move we are bringing the knight to f6. The a8-knight will still be trapped even on the c7 square! }
15. Qd3 Nf6 16. Be3 Ne4+ 17. Kc1 { 17.Ke1  Re8  the white king suffers. } 17...
Ba3+ 18. Kb1 Qa5 { threatening to take on c3. } 19. Bd4 Bf5
{ And we are taking the a8 knight and being only an exchange down, Black's attack is too dangerous and White's position collapses. }
