13... Nd7 14. Nxa8
{ Again, I would like to say that it is important to memorize these chapter lines because we are in the streets with a rook down. But again, the good news is that Black is perfectly fine! }
14... Bc5
{ After this move we are bringing the knight to f6. The a8-knight will still be trapped even on the c7 square! }
15. Qg3 { This inaccurate move is the one that Volokitin chose. } 15... Nf6
{ Ne4 is again the idea and now even stronger because the queen is on g3. } 16.
Re1 { Is the best try for White, but after } 16... Ne4+ 17. Rxe4 dxe4+ 18. Ke1
Bf5 19. Nc7 Qd7
{ Black will eventually capture the knight on c7 with Bb6 and Rc8 with a better position. }
