dxc4 17. Be5 { This is White's idea. The bishop covers now b2. } 17... Re8
{ threatening f6 and forcing White to go for } 18. Bc3 Qb5+ 19. Ka1 Rxe3 20.
Rd8+ Bf8 21. fxe3 Qa4
{ With an equal position according to the engines. I recommend you to play a little bit at home to understand better the position. }
22. Rxc8 { If  22.Rc1?  Bf5  and Black is better. } 22... Qxc2 23. Bb4 c5 24.
Bxc5 Qc3+ 25. Kb1 Qd3+ { with perpetual } *

