{ Now c5 does not gain any tempo so we are going to propose a very interesting pawn sacrifice! Besides, it is a novelty :@@EndBracket@@ }
12... c6
{ Black's idea is to push with d5.   If White does accept the challenge and takes the d6-pawn, Black will have tremendous play as shown in the following analysis. }
13. Kb1
{ If White does not accept the challenge then Black should strike in the center. }
13... d5 14. g5
{ 14.e5?  Nd7  and Black is much better. Bb4 is a nasty idea.   If White retreats the knight to e2 to avoid the pin then Black can push with c5, with a super queenside pawn structure. }
14... Nh5 15. Be3 d4
{ This move is possible because the g5 pawn will hang as well. } 16. Qxd4 Qa5
{ with b4 coming, so White must trade queens with } 17. Qb6 Qxb6 18. Bxb6 Bxg5
{ Reaching a balanced endgame and I would say a little easier to play in practice for Black because of the structure. }
