19... Bg4 20. Rd2 { allows } 20... d5 21. e5
{ White cannot take the pawn by playing  21.exd5?  because after  Qxa4!  Black wins a piece. }
21... Rad8 22. Bf3
{ White wants to trade bishops and put a lot of pressure on d5, but Black has a nice resource. }
22... d4 { forcing } 23. Bxc6 dxe3 24. Rg2 Bd7 25. Bf3 g6 26. Nb2 Bb5
{ followed by Rd4, putting pressure on f4. } 27. Re1 Rd4 28. Bxh5 gxh5 29. Rxe3
Red8
{ Reaching a very interesting endgame where White is a pawn up but Black has active rooks and the bishop pair.  Ideas: h6 and Bd7.   The bishop can land on e6, f5, or g4. }
