17. Nxb5 Re8 18. Nf3 Bd5 { now black is intending to play a6 followed by Qxb2 }
19. b3 Bc5 20. Qd2 Ng4 { all the infantry against the facundo pawn! } 21. Rf1
Bxf3 22. gxf3 Ne5
{ and despite being two pawns up, it is white the one that needs to play accurately. }
23. Be2 Qf6 24. Qd5 Bf8 25. c4
{ being greedy means losing in this case after the simple } 25... Ng6
{ followed by Re5 with a mating attack. } *

