{ has been played in 8 games according to my database. } 13... Ng4
{ crazy complications will come now! } 14. h3 Bc5 15. Ne2
{ and now Black has an easy way to make a draw with  15...Qh4  , as we can see in the next variation. }
15... h5
{ it is a superinteresting try to go for the win! The point is that the bishop on f3 hasn't got room. }
16. c3 f6 17. Ng3 fxe5 18. fxe5 Rxe5 19. hxg4 Rxe1+ 20. Qxe1 hxg4 21. Bd1 Nxd4
22. cxd4 Bxd4+ 23. Be3 Qe7 24. Nf1 Bxb2 25. Rb1 Bf6
{ reaching a mega crazy position. Black has four pawns for the piece. The engines say is around equal, but frankly speaking I would take black. It feels that white can collapse much easier. If you are going to play this line, check it a bit! }
