{ In this chapter we study the move 5.h3, a very aggressive try from white.   Usually, the idea will be to push g4 immediately or near future, starting a dangerous attack on the kingside.  Strong GMs such as Antipov or Krasenkow, went for this variation.   This is one of my favorite chapters since black will sacrifice pawns and pieces in many lines! }
5... Be7 6. Be3 { is the other serious move for white here. } 6... c6
{ Black starts with this move delaying castling. It prepares a queenside expansion as usual. }
7. a4 { White stops b5.   7.g4  h5  transposes to 6.g4 } 7... O-O 8. Be2
{ Black can deviate from the main lines now with the strong } 8... d5 9. Nxe5
Nxe4 10. Nxe4 dxe4 11. Nxd7 Bxd7
{ and the position is around equal. Be6 and f5 are some ideas. } *

