{ and at this crossroads, white has employed three different moves. } 11. Nd2
{ The best try for white. With this move, white overprotects e4 so the knight on c3 can retreat to e2 if needed. }
11... exd4 12. Bxd4 b5 13. f4
{ Was seen in Salaun, Y  @@StartBracket@@2391@@EndBracket@@-Guadalpi, D @@StartBracket@@2282@@EndBracket@@ ½-½ France 2001. White is threatening to push e5 so Black plays the prophylactic }
13... Re8 14. Bf2 Bf8
{ reaching a very interesting position. Black can continue with Qc7-Rad8. c5 will be always a possibility and also g6 followed by Bg7. }
