{ In this chapter we analyze the move 5.Be2.   When our opponents go for these set-ups, it usually means that they do not have a clue of how to fight against the Philidor or that they do not want to enter in the theoretical lines for some reason.   The c4 square is a much better one for the bishop since from there it attacks f7, which is the weakest Black square. This is why this move is considered to be less critical but anyway there are more than 1000 games with this line, so definitely deserve serious attention.   It is a normal developing move and White gets ready to castle.   I am pretty sure you will see it pretty often in your games, so let's study how to handle these positions! }
