11... b4
{ I personally lost one OTB game with this move. It is a move that was considered dangerous for Black 5-10 years ago, but Stockfish 12 finds that is completely fine for Black.   It will be important to remember the whole line, but nothing different from the rest of this crazy chapter! }
12. Na4
{ The first time I saw this move was over the board in a classical game against an IM. I could not believe this was working for white, but it was in fact home preparation and I ended up losing pretty soon.   It is extremely dangerous! }
12... Qxa4
{ This is what I did in my game but now white gets a decisive attack after }
13. Nxe5 Qa5 { bringing the queen back does not help either. } 14. Nxc6 Qc7 15.
e5 Ne4 16. Qd5 Bb7 17. Bb5 Bxc6 18. Bxc6 O-O-O 19. Qxe4 *

