Nb6 15. f4 O-O { we prioritize the king's safety. } 16. f5
{ If  16.fxe5?  then  Ng4 } 16... Nxa4 17. bxa4 Bxf5
{ a fantastic move! Black will bring a rook to d8 soon and then will make use of the c3 square. }
18. exf5 Rad8 19. Qe2 Rxd1+ 20. Qxd1 Nd5 21. Bd2 Qc5
{ Black has two pawns for the piece and a much better king. Nc3 ideas are extremely dangerous opening the b-file.   In practice, White will collapse pretty easily even though the position is about equal according to the engines. }
