1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. g4
{ Straight to the jugular.   White sacrifices a pawn and will get a lot of counterplay along the g-file, making it difficult for Black to develop the f8-bishop in many variations.   Black should take the pawn }
5... Nxg4 6. Rg1 Ngf6
{ And from this point we divide the chapter into two parts.   We first analyze the lines where White goes  7.Bc4  and then the lines where White does not play 7.Bc4 and instead tries to rapidly develop the queenside.   Both are very dangerous. }
7. Bc4
{ Perhaps the most natural move. White is already threatening to win with the move Ng5 because f7 suffers. Now we give two interesting alternatives for black. }
7... h6 { Prophylaxis against Ng5. The main line by far. } 8. Be3
{ White starts developing the queenside, because its short term plan is to castle longside. Black will struggle developing the kingside because of the pressure along the g-file. That is why black main moves will be focused on the queenside. }
8... c6
{ a very typical move that we have seen many times. Black controls d5, and prepares an expansion on the queenside with b5. }
9. dxe5 { The main line. } 9... dxe5 10. Qd3
{ white protects the e4-pawn and is ready to castle. } 10... b5 11. Bxf7+
{ I am 100% sure that many of you will face this move in practice many times. In my case, I have played at least 10 times this position in rapid tournaments. This capture on f7 is very tempting for white because white gets a queen, but black gets enough material for the queen and objetively will be better. }
11... Kxf7 12. Nxe5+ Nxe5 13. Qxd8 Nf3+
{ this is the point. Black gets the rook in g1 as well. } 14. Kd1 Nxg1
{ Too fast Pepe! Let's count the pieces. Black has a rook and two pieces for the queen, which is more than enough. Still the position is complicated so we will have to make couple of precise moves to consolidate our advantage. }
15. Kc1 { The king hides   15.Qc7+  Be7  16.Kc1  transposes } 15... Nf3
{ This is maybe the most natural move bringing the knight back but it is actually a mistake and white has decent chances after }
16. e5 Nxe5 17. Qc7+ Nfd7 18. f4
{ and c6 is falling with good chances for White } *

