11... h6 { is the first Stockfish 12 choice. Let's dig a little bit! } 12. Qg3
{ using the fact that black should not take on e4. Bh6 deserves some attention too. }
12... Nc5
{ 12...Nxe4?  runs into  13.Nxe4  Rxe4  14.Nf5  Kh7  15.Nxd6!  and Black suffers. }
13. f3
{ 13.Bxh6?  is a blunder because of  Nfxe4  and eventually White's queen will have to leave the g-file and Black will just capture the bishop on h6. }
13... d5 14. e5 { with this natural move white loses a pawn after } 14... Nh5
15. Qe1 f6 { Followed by fxe5. } *

