{ 8.b3  h6  Re1  Transposes to the main chapter of this course.   The same applies to  8.b3  h6  9.Bb2  Re8  10.Re1 }
8... h6
{ After  8...b6?!  9.Qe2!  is very strong. I spent many hours analyzing that position but I think White is just better. }
9. Be3 { 9.Re1  Transposes to another chapter. } 9... Re8 10. dxe5
{ 10.Ba2  transposes to 8.Ba2   10.Re1  transposes to the  (7.Re1)  chapter }
10... dxe5 11. Qe2 Qc7 12. Nh4 Nf8 13. Nf5 Bxf5 14. exf5 N8d7 15. Rfd1
{ Was played in Schlechter,C-Burn,A 1-0 Breslau 1912 and I suggest you to play }
15... e4
{ Black is very healthy and ready to play a5 followed by Rad8.   Qe5 @@StartBracket@@targetting f5@@EndBracket@@-Bd6 is always painful for white.   The bishop pair is highly compensated. }
