{ And the reader will not be able to avoid a smile.   What is that rook doing on b4?   It is super interesting and black is ready to give up the exchange on c4 if needed. }
17. Rad1 Ncd7
{ The bishop on c4 managed to be out of the pawn chain but of course it is more exposed.   Ne5 is the idea. }
18. Bf4 { Prophylaxis. White is ready to take on e5. } 18... d5
{ Boom!   Black creates chaos and the center is blown up. } 19. exd5 Rxe1+ 20.
Rxe1 Nb6 { The knight on d4 is unprotected. } 21. Qd3 Nxc4 22. bxc4 cxd5 23.
cxd5 Nxd5 24. Nde2 { There is a nasty pin along the d-file but Black holds. }
24... Be6 25. Rd1 { If  25.Rd1  Black can play } 25... Qe7
{ The e2-knight is hanging after the trades.   The queen sacrifice after  25...Nxc3!?  26.Qxd8  Nxe2+  27.Kh2  Nxf4=  Is also super interesting to play for the win. }
26. Nxd5 Bxd5 27. Qxd5 Qxe2 *

