14. Qd3 b5 15. b4
{ And we arrive to a very similar position to the critical line where Black plays 8...b6 , but with several tempi up for black :@@EndBracket@@ }
15... exd4 16. Bxd4 Ne5 17. Qe3 Bf8
{ Black is fine and it is ready to play Be6, trading the light-squared bishops and therefore c4 will be a really tasty square. }
