{ White prepares a fianchetto on the queenside.   The bishop can land on a3 as well increasing pressure on d6.   10...Qc7  is the main line now but we again go for a direct approach after }
10... exd4 11. Nxd4 Bf8 12. Ba3
{ Was seen in Prohorov, O @@StartBracket@@2086@@EndBracket@@ -Pikula,D @@StartBracket@@2415@@EndBracket@@ 0-1 Chess.com INT 2020. We recommend }
12... a6
{ Creating some tricks in the short-term.   The thing is that if black manages to play b5 attacking the bishop on c4, this will have to be moved and then b4! sacrificing a pawn would win the game because after Bxb4 c5! forks and black wins a piece. Of course c6 must be protected before trying b5.   In similar positions some people have fallen for this trick in my games, definitely good to know about this idea! }
13. Bf1 { Prophylaxis } 13... Ne5 14. Bb2 { 14.Qd2  b5  transposes. } 14... Bd7
{ And Black has good play. The idea is to proceed with Ng6 and b5 if allowed. }
*

